data.enText: a holiday/vacation taken by a couple who have just got married

data.chText: 我们去威尼斯度的蜜月。
data.enText: We went to Venice for our honeymoon.
the period of time at the start of a new activity when nobody is criticized and people feel enthusiastic

data.chText: 这届政府的蜜月期现在已经过去了。
data.enText: The honeymoon period for the government is now over.

tr: a holiday taken by a newly married couple
the early (usually calm and harmonious) period of a relationship
spend a holiday after one's marriage
example: they plan to honeymoon in Hawai'i

value.def: A honeymoon is a holiday taken by a man and a woman who have just got married.
When a recently-married couple honeymoon somewhere, they go there on their honeymoon.

example.tran: 他们在威尼斯度了蜜月。
正在度蜜月的日本游客

value.def: You can use honeymoon to refer to a period of time after the start of a new job or new government when everyone is pleased with the person or people concerned and is nice to them.

example.ex: Austrians voted for EU membership by a two-to-one majority in a June 1994 referendum, but the honeymoon is definitely over...
example.tran: 奥地利在1994年6月举行的全民公决中以2比1的多数票支持加入欧盟，但这一蜜月期明显已经结束了。

example.ex: Brett is enjoying a honeymoon period with both press and public.
example.tran: 布雷特和报界及公众之间都正处在蜜月期。

value.tran: （新工作开始或新政府成立后的）和谐时期，蜜月期
